# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   For an app, you probably want it ignored.
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or not
#   install all needed dependencies.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Poetry uses pyproject.toml to manage dependencies and isolates them in a virtualenv.
#   Poetry users should generally commit the poetry.lock file.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   PDM stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml
.pdm.toml
.pdm-plugins/

